Yes, this flowchart can absolutely be turned into a web-based workflow application using Python (with Flask or Django) for the backend and HTML/CSS/JS for the frontend. Below is a simple Flask-based implementation of this flow with placeholders for each step.

ð§ 1. Python (Flask) Backend

Save the following code as app.py:

python
from flask import Flask, render_template, request, redirect, url_for

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def start():
    return render_template('start.html')

@app.route('/register')
def register():
    return render_template('register.html')

@app.route('/login')
def login():
    return render_template('login.html')

@app.route('/account_created')
def account_created():
    return render_template('link_id.html')

@app.route('/link_id', methods=['POST'])
def link_id():
    link = request.form.get('link_id')
    if link == 'yes':
        return redirect(url_for('health_profile'))
    else:
        return redirect(url_for('health_profile'))

@app.route('/health_profile')
def health_profile():
    return render_template('health_profile.html')

@app.route('/genetic_test', methods=['POST'])
def genetic_test():
    result = request.form.get('genetic')
    return render_template('preprocessing.html', uploaded=(result == 'yes'))

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(debug=True)
